					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13126192#post-4541301</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13126192/scp-5408#post-4541301</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 11 Mar 2020 02:17:04 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Rigen</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2826105</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Imma just crit this one line:</p> <blockquote> <p>This radiation was similar to that used in microwave ovens, but at an exponentially greater concentration,</p> </blockquote> <p>I don't think people usually speak of electromagnetic radiation in terms of &quot;concentration&quot;? Probably want &quot;power&quot; there. The first clause is kinda a major tone break, maybe you could change it to something more like &quot;The emitted electromagnetic radiation was detected within the 2.4&#160;GHz range&quot; and then have a footnote explaining it as the Industrial, Scientific, and Medical band that is also in use by microwave oven?</p> <p>otherwise +1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
